President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Wisconsin due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred from July 18 to July 20, 2019. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in certain counties and tribal areas. Hazard mitigation measures will also be eligible for federal funding. Steven W. Johnson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.